welcome_guide.body: Due to neighborhood restrictions, parties are not allowed in this home. Disregarding this rule will result in immediate eviction.

welcome_guide.body: Check-out is at 10:00 am. We hope you had a wonderful stay.

welcome_guide.title: No Smoking
welcome_guide.body: No smoking is allowed on the premises. If smoking does occur on the premises, Guest may be evicted and is financially responsible for all damage caused by the smoking including, but not limited to, stains, burns and the cost of odor remediation and removal and replacement of damaged property.

welcome_guide.title: Noise and Neighbors
welcome_guide.body: Please be aware that even normal conversation amplifies off the buildings in higher density neighborhoods. As a courtesy to your neighbors, please minimize loud conversation, music, and general noise, especially after 10:00 pm. Please be respectful at all times, and be aware that the San Diego Noise Ordinance is strictly enforced. Neighbors will notify Bluewater and/or the police regarding disturbances. If Law Enforcement is dispatched due to any illegal activities or disturbances originating from the property, it is considered grounds for fines and/or immediate eviction. If any neighbors are disturbing you, please call Bluewater during normal business hours, or the San Diego Police after-hours.

welcome_guide.title: Safety & Security
welcome_guide.body:
Vacating the home quickly can be very important in case of an emergency. Please ensure all occupants take a moment to become familiar with the layout of the home and identify all exit routes.
Although, this is generally a safe neighborhood, there are some basic precautionary steps you can take to make sure your stay remains stress-free. Don’t leave items unattended outside or in open garages. Don’t leave any valuables in outside or in plain sight, keep car doors locked, and make sure to lock all windows and doors when leaving the home. If you see any suspicious activity, call 911.

welcome_guide.title: Hot Tub and/or Pool
welcome_guide.body: The house has a private hot tub.

welcome_guide.title: Inventory/Starter Kits
welcome_guide.body:
You will find the home is stocked with all the basics:

- Ready-made beds and at least 1 bath towel, hand towel and wash cloth per guest
- Kitchen stocked with glasses, dishes, and utensils, as well as basic cookware
- The kitchen starter kit includes: hand soap, sponge, dish soap, dishwasher tabs, a roll of paper towels, and kitchen trash bags 
- Each bathroom is equipped with a starter kit which includes a hotel-style set of bath soap, shampoo, conditioner, and two rolls of toilet paper
- Laundry detergent 

The starter kits provided are complimentary and are meant to cover your needs before you get to the store to do your shopping. You may find supplies that have been left by other guests which you are welcome to use, but make sure to take a quick inventory before you shop to ensure you have everything you will need during your stay.

welcome_guide.title: Accidental Damages
welcome_guide.body: Your rental agreement includes a security deposit protection plan. The home will be inspected after departure. Please make sure that you notify Bluewater of any damages prior to departure, otherwise, the security deposit protection is void and your credit card will be charged for the cost of repair/replacement. The most common damages include stains on towels, linens, and carpet. If damage is found to be excessive, or caused by negligence it will not be covered under the policy.

welcome_guide.title: Checkout Procedures
welcome_guide.body:
When it’s time to leave, we recommend checking closely for personal items with a room by room sweep, including all drawers, cabinets, closets, under the beds, and outlets (for chargers), etc.
 
Please leave the property in the same general condition you found it at Check-In, meaning:
 
-Trash picked up and removed from the home
-Discard any perishables, however, you are welcome to leave unopened food or drinks for donation.
-Dishes are cleaned and put away, or started in the dishwasher
-Any cooking messes are cleaned up
-Used towels are placed in the bath tubs or showers (linens can be left in bedrooms)
-Replace any furniture or items that have been rearranged (interior and exterior)
-TV remote controls left in their appropriate rooms in plain sight
-Keys and garage remotes (if applicable) left on the kitchen counter
-Turn-off all lights, air conditioner, heater, fans, etc.
-  *Please make sure all the doors and windows are locked upon departure.*
 
**Please note: Late departures that are not pre-approved in writing, homes that are left excessively dirty, and missing remotes and keys will result in additional charges**
 
Please let us know if you have any questions and thank you for staying with Bluewater!

welcome_guide.title: Environmental Considerations
welcome_guide.body: Southern California has an arid climate and typically experiences drought conditions. Water restrictions are in effect, so please conserve water accordingly. *When leaving the property, please turn off any extra lights and turn down the heater to save electricity*. Thank you very much!

welcome_guide.title: Emergencies
welcome_guide.body: Please call our office at 858-605-1497 if you have any maintenance emergency. Call 911 in case of fire or other emergencies. In the event of a fire or any major issues, please contact us after everyone is safe.

welcome_guide.title: Outdoor Furniture
welcome_guide.body: When the BBQ and outdoor furniture are not in use we ask that you please use the covers to protect from the elements. Thank you!

welcome_guide.title: Late Checkout
welcome_guide.body: If you would like to request a late checkout, please contact our office before 6pm the day before your departure to see if we are able to grant this for you.

welcome_guide.title: Miscellaneous Items
welcome_guide.body:
- When returning home from the beach, please rinse all sand off outside and shake out towels, etc. prior to entering the home.
- Please do not smoke on the premises.
- Due to safety concerns, please do not light candles.
- No pets allowed on premises, we provide allergen free homes.
- Personal belongings such as bikes, chairs, coolers, towels, etc. should be put in the house or garage for security. 
- The bikes and other beach equipment locked in the garage are the private property of the owners and not for guest use. Please see our Vendor Partners email for a list of vendors who can help you with renting such items.

welcome_guide.title: Recycling
welcome_guide.body: The environment is everyone’s concern and recycling plays an important part of helping conserve. However, due to certain constraints, some homes may not have recycling bins. In the beach alleys, recycling bins attract scavengers who rummage through the bins late at night to illegally collect recyclables, leaving strewn trash behind. In such high-density communities, sometimes there isn’t enough room for trash and recycle bins, so others will place refuse in the recycle bins and the city will not empty those containers, leading to unsanitary conditions. We have tried locking the bins, but if guests do not unlock in time for collection, the bins will stay full and there is not enough room for overflow. We are petitioning the city for other solutions and apologize for any inconvenience this may cause you. If you have any concerns or suggestions, we welcome your call.

welcome_guide.title: Coffee Maker
welcome_guide.body: We provide standard multi-cup drip coffee makers in our homes.

reviews.text: The boat tour was amazing. We got to experience so much and see a lot of wildlife. Jane and Randy were so friendly and knowledgeable. We would go again and again if we lived in the California area. This is a must do when in the San Diego area.

My Aunt came to visit me from Florida, having never been to CA before, this had to be special! So, we booked a charter with San Diego Boat Tours with Tawanna as our Hostess and although it was cloudy that morning, the sun came out and we all had the most amazing and photogenic adventure we could have asked for! Sea lions, pelicans, dolphins, great food and the best tour guide Tawanna, who made the trip truly memorable!

We did a group tour and really enjoyed it.  It was a good value for the money.  We visited four different wineries.  Each one was unique.  The right amount of time was spent at each winery.  We especially enjoyed the other people in our group.  When I visit Sandman/Napa again I would definitely use San Diego Boat Tours again.

We always end up with a great tour guide and tour group (strangers, that after stop #1 become fast friends.) I will continue using them for my visits to wine country and highly recommend to others!

Highly recommend!

reviews.text: Had an amazing time! Saw hundreds of dolphins and a few whales. Our captain Christine was very knowledgeable and made the experience super fun!

Can’t say anything negative! Great price, great guide (Christine), amazing and really fun experience! We saw 3 California Gray whales and also found a maternity pod of dolphins. Christine was so knowledgeable, patient, professional, and also so in love with showing people the ocean and its rich life. It was much better than I ever expected. Highly recommended. Do it!

Had an amazing time! It was an awesome up close experience that is worth every penny! Christine is a wonderful guide and was super knowledgeable and friendly. She made the experience that much more memorable. We saw a nursery pod of bottle nose dolphins with a few baby dolphins that looked like they were just born. They were the cutest little things. We also saw a MEGA pod of dolphins, seemed like we saw over 1000 dolphins! Absolutely incredible. The dolphins get right up to the side of the boat, like two feet from your face! Jumping in the air right next to you. You need to go see this!

This was the best experience ever! The boat is not as small as some of the pictures show, its actually quite sturdy and fast! This helps because you can get to locations where a whale is spotted by the many people sharing information over the radio.

Our captain Christine was very friendly and made us feel secure. She knew the waters really well and had a lot of information to share on the whales, dolphins and sea lions that she has seen so far. Since there were only 6 people onboard it gave a feeling of a more private tour than the larger boats.

We were able to spot a grey whale and a lot of dolphins. We also saw a few sea lions playing about in the water which was really cute as well.

Wow, what a great time!  Christine was our captain.  She is very knowledgeable and friendly.  It was a fun experience.  We got to see some whales and dolphins and got escorted back into the marina by a sea lion.  A really great experience.  Next time I'm back in San Diego I will do this again.  I highly recommend!

reviews.text:
Took the family out last weekend 1/18 and had an enjoyable voyage. Weather was great and we were able to see 3-4 gray whales, plus some California Sea Lions, and a variety of birds. 

Reservations were easy to make and I’d strongly recommend doing so. We found plenty of parking on the street and a short walk to check in. General boarding lined up along the fence and it actually got a little warm in the sun. A small awning for shade would have been nice, but it reminded us we should have brought sunscreen and the nearby Marina store was open and reasonable. 

Our Boat (Privateer) was roomy, clean, and had plenty of outside seating. Captain did his best to make sure everyone on both sides had opportunities to see the whales. Guests were free to move about. Crew was very good and helpful when one of my kids started feeling ill providing remedies and checking in on us. Snack bar has a variety of refreshments and even binoculars available for rent. The biologist provided just the right amount of information about the area and whale behavior with out overwhelming us with details. 

Overall a great day.

This was such a great trip! Even if we didn't see gray whales, dolphins, and sea lions (which we did), I would still highly recommend the SD Whale Watch group. They were extremely helpful and informative throughout the whole trip; they also provided pictures. We booked 2 whale watching trips on back to back days from 2 different companies...SD Whale Watch was by far the better company.

We had a great time on our whale tour! While out we saw a grey whale calf with its mother, a couple other grey whales, a pod of a couple hundred dolphins, and some other marine animals such as sea lions , and pelicans. I would highly recommend! The crew was friendly and very knowledgeable! We used a Groupon and got a great deal. We went when there weren’t maybe people in February and we got to move all around the boat whenever we wanted. Also had snacks and drinks on board. We bought binoculars for $5 as well and my husband really liked using those. Lots of fun!

Excellent tour with this company! Went in mid-January and saw so many sea lions, dolphins, and SIX gray whales! They make sure to give you plenty of viewing time during the 2 hour tour. I was highly impressed with their skill in finding whales and enjoyed my time aboard the Privateer immensely.

What an amazing experience! I’ve lived my
Entire life not believing I would ever be a person to see a humpback whale and today, I saw two! We also were able to ride along with hundreds of dolphins. The tour guide was very informative And the staff was so ridiculously helpful and friendly! Make sure you bring cash so you can purchase hot chocolate or a mimosa! Not to mention being able to tip the awesome team! Three hours was just the right amount of time!

reviews.text: What a great time! We booked a 1/2 day through Coletta Sportfishing and it was an awesome time deep sea fishing in San Diego! Our captain, Jon, and his deckhand, Trevor, were personable and great to spend 5.5 hours with! We ended up catching over 35 Rock Fish, which Trevor did a great job having them ready for us to take home by the time we got back.  These two know their stuff and especially know where the fish are swimming! Next time I go deep sea fishing in San Diego, I absolutely will go through Coletta Sportfishing again! Best in San Diego!

All were over 36” hell of a day on the Swell Chaser! A little sore today!  We quadrupled up twice and had multiple fish on all day long! Ended our half day trip with 23 yellowtail and a few sand bass. All were caught casting on lures and no bait! True definition of sport fishing! I have an outfitting business of my own on the fresh water and Was extremely impressed with Coletta! Excellent service and catching one after another for the entire trip! Thanks guys!

Charter two boats with Captain Chris Coletta.  We had an awesome experience!  If you want to have an amazing experience and catch a lot of fish, book your Sportfishing trip with Coletta!  
Big shout out to the captain's and shipmates for working hard to make our experience perfect!

My father and I booked a full day offshore trip with Coletta Sportfishing for early November in hopes to find some tuna.  Chris Coletta called me shortly after booking to let me know that the tuna bite could be great or it could be nonexistent by that time.  He informed me that we would play it by ear.  If the offshore bite was good, we would go offshore.  If the bite was inconsistent, then it would be best to change our trip to a 3/4 day inshore trip.  When time came for our trip, the tuna had moved on.  Chris called me to let me know and promptly refunded me the price difference.  We met our captain, John, and first mate, Matt at the dock at 6:30.  They were prompt, professional, and easy to fish with. And these guys really know how to put their clients on fish. Overall we caught 7 different species and left with a great bounty of meat for the freezer.  I am supremely grateful that Chris and his crew suggested the trip change.  It was an awesome experience.   recommend Coletta Sportsfishing to anyone, (novice or experienced) for their supreme courtesy and professionalism.

Amazing experience!!! I knew from the first call to Chris Coletta that Coletta Sportfishing was going to be amazing. Professional, knowledgeable and hard working group. Captain Hale and Matt were able to get us into some amazing fish....limited out! I will booking additional trips and strongly recommend if you are reading this and considering sport fishing in San Diego don't look any further.... Call Chris at Coletta Sportfishing!

reviews.text:
I didn’t know what to expect. I was stuck in San Diego with my mother after watching my second child graduate from Boot Camp at the Marine Corps Recruit Depot.

We had several hours to kill, just waiting for planes. I saw the sign underneath a rather impressive collection of architecture and history expertly arranged an built into the hills of San Diego.

I knew that the tour was going to be a combination of history and religious evangelism.  These wonderfully nice people still surprised me.

We arrived halfway through the Spanish tour whereupon a blue eyed latter-day Saints sister recited, by script, in perfect Spanish, a preview of the tour we were about to undertake.

It’s not really a tour.
It is an interactive, three part,(audience, sister tour guides, and interactive historical characters in wall paintings straight out of Harry Potter) historical/spiritual message.

The set dressings are surprisingly realistic given the setting. We know that these are props however, the props are REALLY good!
Like “actual kit or better” good.
( I’m a little bit of a history buff and I have some long years in set design)
The explanations and actual physical props from the US military in that time are spot on accurate from an equipment point of view.
The history side is better than expected. However, this is still a mission. So expect a spiritual side.

At this point I have to tell you, it’s actually an astoundingly positive thing. I wasn’t expecting that.
At the beginning of this they bring up a focusing (at least for me)theme

Throughout tribulation, “We chose to be happy” outlined the Latter Day Saints contributions to both California and to the United States of America.

It was nice to see people who were proud of their faith outlining exactly how that same faith helped frame the west.

Thank you for an entertaining and informational afternoon.

PS: There are many who look at this place as a straight on religious conversion center.  You might be right.

But, at least these people speak from the heart as to what they believe

Fantastic experience! Highly recommend for people of all religious backgrounds. Make reservations in advance to ensure you get in! Super interactive tour. Our two year old even was entertained during the tour and LOVED panning for gold at the end.

Our whole family had a fantastic time learning about the history of the Mormon Battalion and how their efforts paved the way for future historical events. The kids especially liked panning for gold and taking home fools good. It was a fun hour and be sure to make a reservation.

This is a hidden gem in Old Town. I highly recommend it! Very interesting presentation on how the Mormons came to San Diego and were involved in the building of Old Town. Great for the whole family. No charge. Won't even take donations. You can pan for gold at the end.

A hidden gem in Old Town San Diego.  Educational and entertaining at the same time...a movie, museum, old time photo, and gold panning.  Best of all it was all free.  Expect to spend at least an hour here.

reviews.text: I have nothing negative to say about this place. Great view. Great service. I had a great cocktail. And the shrimp and grits were amazing. Spicy, savory, delicious. The spicy mango margarita was great, just the right amount of tequila. We started with the loaded fries, they were really good, sauce not too heavy, just the right amount of toppings. My dad had the draft Burger, looked really good, he enjoyed it. I will definitely be coming back!

Draft is renowned for its views, location, and big screens but the service has been cut to be miserable. Expect to wait 15-20 minutes before placing your order and another 20 or more before a beer arrives. When your food arrives, wait another 15 minutes before you can get a setup. Your over worked server will be apologetic but it won't make up for the lack of service or attention to detail. They need 3 to 4 more servers at least

I stopped by here to watch a football game. Really nice restaurant with a nice ambiance. I ordered the cauliflower buffalo. it's a nice vegetable option. Parking is free and they have their own lot. Not much of a wait unless a big game is on.

reviews.text:
I started working down the street from Gelson's two years ago - I occasionally stop in for the salad bar and hot bar on my lunch break. The food is always excellent and fresh, you can tell someone is consistently checking on the food here. 

More importantly, the customer service here is excellent. They work to reduce the long waits in lines. The store itself may be a bit more expensive than your typical grocery store, but the customer service and general cleanliness of the store explains why. I'm happy to continue shopping here.
Time and time again we experience first class service, and always with a smile. Teresa was a perfect example this evening! Always kind and sincere; a rare find these days. Thank you team Gelson’s!

Omg they have a fresh 🥗 salad 🥗 bar! I was with undecicive people & hungry & also had to pee so I headed to this grocery store where I passed this beautiful, amazing, fresh salad bar.
I did my business & then headed out to make myself a salad (yes I washed my hands) & they had pretty much everything I would put on my salad so I got no complaints. 
They are obviously environmentally friendly with their cardboard to go packaging, which a company should be, so close to the ocean. Thank you for that, Gelson's!
If just for the salad bar, I highly recommend!!! 
If you enjoyed this review or found it helpful PLEASE give it a LIKE!
This is a great place to buy "home made" hot and cold food by the pound as well as regular groceries.

Pros: Good selection and convenience.
Cons: Very over priced and customer service is not great.

A co-worker just moved into the neighborhood from Spain and was commenting about how incredibly expensive food is in the United States... my response was simply, “Oh you must be shopping at Gelsons. That’s your first mistake!”
It’s the same staff as when this was a Haggen before, and an Albertsons before that, so I’m really not buying the “cost of labor” canned response.

I’m glad the store exists for the convenience, but they sure do gouge you for it, so shop here sparingly. Getting someone to ring you up can also be a challenge which is surprising given how many people seem to be on shift at any given time.

reviews.text: It was our first time going off shore fishing went with two family friends and he's kids ages 16/18 kids had no experience in fishing so we thought the crew would be more then willing to help but no they were beyond rude with attitude  like we were doing it wrong on purpose.. the crew member who was the most rude was a white male with a white anchor beard was super rude made the kids and our self very uncomfortable and embarrassed .. but there was one man who was super outgoing and chill willing to help with anything he could and was the only chief on and made everyone's food right away I would most definitely hire that guy but the rest of the crew was horrible & bitter  they don't make it fun at all . We go on a Sunday morning to have a beautiful day out with our family enjoy beautiful San Diego not get  belittled  !

Horrible fishing, but hardly their fault. They did what they could to track down the fish, the fish just weren't biting. We could've stuck around longer in each area though. We'd drop lines and then a couple minutes later the captain would tell us to reel in. At least my father-in-law caught one!

The food was AMAZING. One of the best burgers I've ever had. The breakfast sandwich was delicious too.

The deckhand was great. Extremely helpful. Double-checked and fixed any tackles that were tied wrong. Gave a demonstration on the best knot he uses. Great demonstration on the fishing itself as well. Always kept plenty of bait in the bins for us.

Only real issues I have were:
- we set out a bit later than we were supposed to
- 2 boat changes the day before and morning of
- boat was a little crowded at 18 guys going out to fish, would've preferred capping it at maybe 10. obvious they just wanted to make some more cash buy cramming a bit more heads onto the boat
- didn't stick around long enough at each spot
Great trip!  The crew was very helpful and got us onto the fish.  Great food on the boat as well.

July 21st 2017. Debating Point Loma because of Google reviews.  Point Loma is NOT the New Lo An.  Yes, parking sucks and I don't know about the other boats but here is my review of the New Lo An from July 21st, 2017.

Decided to go on the New Lo An since the boat came highly recommended by a friend.  I had never been on the New Lo An before.  The boat has a nice platform for fishing, roomy and double stack rod holders. The galley is smaller than some but comfortable with a nice breeze.  The food was excellent!  Homemade burgers and potato salad. Not like your mom used to make, even better!  Steve is an excellent Chef/Cook. The deckhands were helpful and on point with helping with tangles and tagging fish.  No attitudes or poor service and the fish cleaning was done proficiently and without wast.  Adam was captain on this overnighter and did beyond an excellent job.  We beat the fleet that trip and Adam was definitely the key to that!

The bunk room was a little hot but they are fairly spacious. Be aware that if you get the top bunks in the center of the bunk room they do not have walls separating your neighbor next door but could be nice if you were bringing along the wife.  Mitch's seafood is located on the dock so you can grab some dinner before you head out but set aside some time because they are busy.

All in all I can see why this boat has 5 stars even if Point Loma doesn't.  Nothing bad to say at all.  Thanks for a great trip guys...

Just got back from 1 1/2 day trip. For $370 dollars I was very dissapointed. We were coming in from out of state and were told we didn't need to bring anything they would provide everything.  Ourselves and several others were given the wrong tackle from the shop  and couldnt even fish and when it was brought up there was zero concern from anyone on the boat. We were treated more like a nuisance than  a paying customer. When we came in the guys that gave us the wrong rig chuckled and said"yeah man that's like a knife in a gun fight" really? No attempt to make things right. The right hand doesn't know what the left ones doing and once they have your money they couldn't care anyway. Don't waste your time with this outfit I heard H  and M were decent and will try them next time!

reviews.text: Amazing place to visit! Lots of activities in the area.  in addition to free walking tours around the Old Town with a guide. Lots of great restaurants and shops. Easily can spent several hours there. Free parking as well, but parking lot is not big so better arrive before noon.

I loved Old Town SD. We took the Old Town Trolley Tours which was a fantastic way to learn the history of the area. Don and Larry, our drivers, were kind and entertaining through the rides. The other very cool thing was that you can get off at any of the several stops along the way and pick up the story with the next trolley you board.

Old Town Orange is a beautiful small city to take a walk at night. The people are very friendly and welcoming to tourists. 

The variety of things that you find at this place are breathtaking. Some of the cool things you can find here vary from cacao grinding stones to live music to ancient tobacco smoking pipes.

This place is also home to some of the most well taken care of Adobe houses. The beauty of its clay barrel roofs is complete perfection. This small town is like going back in time to the times Pancho Sevilla.

We came here looking for an educational adventure and we were very happy with the results.
Every single one of the staff at Wells Fargo museum was very pleasant and very knowledgeable. They really "live" up to their character and seem happy to share what they know.
Definitely a good free experience.

This is such a fun spot to visit!  I've been here several times since my first trip to San Diego about 12 years ago but recently I brought a co-worker for a business trip and he had never been so I was able to show him around and eat lunch here. 

I love that this is open and free to the public and the space is also educational as well as historic.  There are some functioning open shops where they sell items that are handcrafted and of course the kitschy items everyone wants like masks and brightly painted skulls. 

The staff who work here are very friendly and engaging and will literally pull you in off the street to give demonstrations and teach you about the historic significance of the buildings and location. 

Great food here and some shopping as well.

reviews.text: Amazing day!!!  Our tour guide, Paris, was extremely insightful about all 3 wineries and the history of the land.  We learned so much and tried 18 wonderful wines.  Everything went smoothly from one vineyard to the next and there was a chance to relax and enjoy the scenery at each stop!  Our group had a blast together, laughs throughout the entire day!  I would most definitely recommend this tour for anyone!

PLEASE read if you want honest review.

Let me start by saying it was a fun tour and the tour guide was very knowledgeable and friendly.

The problem is this is not a wine train, nor should it be advertised as so on their website.

Most of the tour is in local San Diego. You do take a train that allows you to see about 30 seconds of the coast. I am convinced taking this public train is only so they can advertise as a “wine train” 

My friends and I are local to San Diego and wanted to try something different. Everything on this tour can be done without a tour guide without spending extra money to take a train.

If anyone is really interested in what a wine train is suppose to be look up Napa Valley wine train.

This tour was amazing. Our tour guide Paris was very knowledgeable and kept a good pace and atmosphere throughout the day. Our tour only involved two groups which made it feel very private. We went to three vineyards and tried 20 wines throughout the day. The first vineyard was called Domain Artifact and was probably where our favourite wines were at. There was a charcuterie platter that had some excellent snacks to pair with the wine. Since our group was small we were able to tour the vineyard and even try a few late grapes off the vine. The second vineyard was called Orfila which was much more lively and had a bit of a wait for wine at the pour area. We were able to go to the back with the casks and see where the grapes were fermenting. The final stop was Bernardo where we were served some delicious salads and pizza. We were able to pair our wines the chocolate and wind down the night in a nice atmosphere. I would 100% recommend this tour to anyone coming to San Diego.

Had such a fantastic time on our chauffeured wine trip! Tiffany was our guide and communicated clearly on pick up time, we had the whole van to our own group (lucky us!) and totally exceeded our expectations. Would do this again in a heartbeat.

Took the VIP chauffeured day trip through three wineries with my mother on our vacation.  Was such an amazing day!  Our guide, Tiffany, was so entertaining, thoughtful, and always kept us informed.  Each winery offered a different experience and the dinner at the end was an amazing location!  There were an abundance of tastings included and our group had a fun time together, even though we started the day as strangers.  Highly recommend this experience!  Well worth the cost!

Not for tourists

 Jet skis are two small for two average sized people. Very easily tipped. 

Oh and if you tip it they charge you a tow fee for $85 then possibly a flood fee for $50 or something. recommendations.tip:
Situated next to Mission Beach, Mission Bay Park is the largest artificial aquatic park in the country. It stretches over 4,235 acres and features 27 miles of shoreline, 19 of which are sandy beaches with eight locations designated as swimming areas. Enjoy boating, swimming, biking, playing sports, picnicking and more.

FISHING
As a spotted bay bass paradise, Mission Bay is one of the most popular locations in San Diego for fishing. Anglers can also fish for halibut, corvina and other sand-dwelling species. Fish from the shore at Bahia Point, Sail Bay and Quivera Basin, or charter a boat from Dana Landing.
*Local tip: Fish during the incoming or outgoing tide as the fish tend to be more active.*

reviews.text: Our Captain Kirk was super great! The ride was exhilarating but safe. 🙂 It really was a great experience. Kirk was fun, funny and very skilled. The ride itself was a blast. We did get a glimpse of whales, dolphins and a sea lion although they did not cooperate fully and were being a little shy. The captain made it entertaining and the views were top notch. If we ever get back here we will definitely be back. Thanks for making our trip memorable.

What a great day!! I booked a whale watching adventure with Adventure Rib Rides and we had some unusually bad weather for San Diego...Adventure Rib Rides was great at contacting me and helping move my adventure to a time when the weather was clearing up. Every wildlife adventure is different and you can't control wild animals, but on our adventure we were able to get up close with some sea lions and some Pacific white-sided dolphins and were treated to seeing 9 gray whales including a calf. Captain Spencer was awesome, explained things in great detail, was very experienced and a lot of fun. I've done some whale watching tours in Alaska and Hawaii on the "big boats" and the experience in the RIB boat does not compare. It is fantastic and well worth a premium price. Highly recommend these guys and if back in the area, I would definitely do a tour with them again.

We had a fun time with Captain Spence on our Adventure Rib Rides Whale Watch. We saw several White Sided Dolphins that were great fun to watch and also saw a gray whale spout several times. Spence was very knowledgeable about ocean life and the San Diego environment in edition to being very personable. He made a real effort to make sure we were comfortable and having a great time during the entire trip. I highly recommend Adventure Rib Rides to anyone who wants to go whale watching. The small (6 passenger) boats provide great viewing  opportunities and personalized service.

This was the best tour I could’ve gone on in all of San Diego! Definitely not what I expected but SO much better. The boat is quick and tiny, not a large cruise liner. Makes the whole experience much more intimate. Kirk was an amazing captain and extremely funny! The furniture and decor is high quality and in great condition. The location of the house can't be beat! Right off the bay with multiple views of the water. The wall of movable glass doors that open fully are a wonderful feature as well. The whole place has a super cool vibe and is designed to perfection. It was perfect for our needs and we really enjoyed staying there. We were attending our son's wedding and multiple activities so we really didn't get a chance to enjoy the area, but I would have loved to do that too. There are cool spots close by!

We had such good experience with Bluewater Vacation Homes, the key is communication. They did a great job letting me know everything. Very professional, yet warm too.  We are easy going folks, so we look for the good in things, and thought everything well very well !
Condo was clean and had everything we thought we would need. Very Well stocked. I will be back for sure. The location was great and walking on the beach was the best. And we Loved San Diego!

Gorgeous property right on the beach!! Rooms are clean and beds are comfortable! You can walk to restaurants, have groceries delivered, etc. The outdoor Fire pit is so nice on a cool evening while enjoying the sunset. You won’t be disappointed. Just book it!! ☺️

Beautiful location, two doors from the palisades park where there’s yoga several times a week. Two doors from Law Street beach. Everything you need, well stocked kitchen, comfy beds, laundry on premises, responsive management team. This was our second year booking this property and it was like a home away from home. Attached to the main house by a two car garage, owners have not been there when we’ve rented. Very well maintained property. Big surf destination. We have lots of family and friends in San Diego having lived there and this is a great place to bring people together and eat, drink and be merry! Front yard has a propane fire pit with six chairs and table with six chairs in the back. Would definitely book again.

The condo was clean and all ready for us when we entered.  We called about two minor things and they sent someone immediately to repair it.  The maintenance men were kind and fun.  They had some "goodies" for us when we arrived.  That was a nice gesture too.  The view from the condo was fantastic.  I would highly recommend this condo to others.  A return trip for us could be in the future.

reviews.text: Really great experience. Went for an evening sail and had a great time.  Captain Terry was phenomenal. Offered really interesting history of San Diego and all of the ships/vessels on the water.  Definitely would go again.  Price point is well worth the experience.  Customer service from owner (Kyle?) was fantastic.  Without going into details, they put the needs of the customer first. I was impressed.

We made a game time decision to take a sunset cruise with San Diego Sailing Tours and I'm so glad that we did. Captain Terry was a delight providing the perfect amount of commentary on our tour. He is very knowledgeable about the area.  We were offered complimentary beverages, a blanket, and he even took photos for us. The sunset views were spectacular. I highly recommend San Diego Sailing Tours.

My wife and I enjoyed our little sailing adventure in the harbor. We arrived in the parking lot and quickly spotted our captain (Allan or Allen), who was looking for us and another couple. Super nice guy. It was a small sail-boat, nothing fancy, but wonderful and enjoyable nonetheless; just us and the other couple and the captain, total 5 people. It was a 2-hour ride and the weather was perfect. They, of course, use the engine to get out and then the sail goes up and the engine goes off and the quiet begins; very nice indeed. Lots of interesting things to see in the harbor, seals, sea-lions, other boats, things in the distance.  Out captain was very knowledgeable about sailing and sites in the harbor. The other couple that went were very delightful, and we all laughed and had a great time together. Again, Captain Allen was fantastic; we enjoyed our little adventure very much and would recommend it without hesitation, it really exceeded what I was expecting.

Beautiful Sunset Sail! The sky,  water and building all light up with color as the sun sets.  The boat offers multiple seats to choose from allowing for different views of the scenery.  The tour included history of serval old ships and random fun facts about the area. I saw dolphins and watched a seaplane land right beside us during sunset. Captain Terri was a great guide and very hospitable.  Overall great experience and highly recommend!!!

-Lina

Captain Allan is great! He has a clear passion for what he does (been sailing since he was 11!) and is extremely knowledgeable about the area.  We were able to set sail a bit early and get some additional time on the water, and the sunset was breathtaking. Definitely a great experience.

Also there is a good lifeguard service at the beach and they are very well-equipped to handle situations. Parking is good unless there is a holiday in which then it will be very crowded and also in the parking spot that we used you don’t have to pay

Great park-especially if you can find parking in the free lot right in front of the beach.  Many restrooms in two locations, a beautiful pier to walk to on the wide boardwalk, and a beautiful, large playground between the beach and the grassy picnic area (that also has grills).  The beach is perfect for swimming, snorkeling and kayaking as it has really easy access without larger breaking waves that you'll find at other local beaches. A gorgeous beach.  Gets very busy though as it's so perfect and close to the college.

Checked this spot out for Happy Hour (~4-7 pm) to meet up with a friend for a drink. The bar was pretty empty when I arrived, but it was a very cool, cavernous space -- perfect for escaping the summer heat. The bartenders were super friendly, greeted me and chatted for a bit, which was nice because it's a bummer when you walk into a place and feel like it's too pretentious for your existence LOL.

reviews.text: Fantastic sailing adventure! Captain Frank was a great host. We were one of two couples on the boat. Saw whales and dolphins. Beauty of the ocean can not be overstated. My husband says it was the best birthday gift ever.

Did the 2 pm whale watching tour with Happy Captain Greg and it was amazing. Happy Captain Greg acts as a tour guide in addition to his captaining duties, which makes for a great trip. We did see whales, multiple times, and the ship holds just 6 per tour so we were comfortable and up close. This is now my go-to tour and I’d highly recommend it to friends and family! (My pix of the whales are in video so just posting the lovely sunset we saw as we returned to port.)

I cannot even do justice with words as to just how pleased and impressed my wife and I were with our experience with Sail San Diego!  It starts with their impeccable accommodation with scheduling.  My wife and I were unable to make our initial flight due to weather in the Midwest and, thus, we were unable to make our initial reservation with Sail San Diego.  The GM, Cal, was extremely understanding and accommodating and kindly shifted our reservation back a day without penalty so we could still get the experience while on our getaway.  

The experience itself was SUPERB!  We were extremely fortunate enough to get Frank as our guide.  Frank, who has several decades of sailing experience, was absolutely wonderful.  He was extremely knowledgeable, a terrific captain, and was one of the most personable tour guides I had ever encountered.  The boats themselves are stunning.  Everything from the deck to the helm and everything in between was plush and very relaxing.  The hospitality they provided was beyond imagination and far superseded our anticipations.  Put it this way, we left with full bellies and a good Chardonnay afternoon buzz (not to worry, we Uber'ed it home).  

We are already planning on coming back and bringing our families so they can also experience Sail San Diego, which proved to be our favorite San Diego experience!  Thank you again Cal, Frank and the Sail San Diego Team!  

Dr. G (Solomon)

Went on a 3 hour sail with Happy Captain Greg and it was a great way to cherish the beautiful city of San Diego! We got the private rental for 6 , the fridge was stocked with beer , wine and snacks. We played our own music, got under blankets, sipped some wine, saw a spectacular sunset. We even saw a cruise ship real close which was cool. It is a slower paced activity, almost meditative :)

We had a spectacular experience! Captain Greg was the right balance of informative and humor.  We got to see dolphins,  seals, and grey whales. Loved having the small party of 6 passengers, freedom to navigate the boat, and take in the California beauty.  Well-stocked boat and Captain is a very skilled sailor. When we observe the large whale-watching ships from afar, they looked packed and uncomfortable. This experience is very much worth the value!

reviews.text: Going here is a lot of fun. This place is amazing since they are always ready to help sea creatures. They take them back to their facility to help them get better then release them back into the wild. This place helps them out. A lot of great rides, shows, and attractions. A fun place to go to an event too.

We went in January 2020 on a Wednesday,  it was the best experience. We were able to park close to the entrance, the longest time we waited in line was maybe 5 minutes if that. We saw most of the shows and were able to sit just about anywhere we wanted because the park was not crowded at all! The staff were friendly and put everything into their show even with the small crowd. I think off season during the week is the best time to visit if you're able.

It is one of the best amusement park based on Sea theme and roller coasters. Nice place to take kids.
It hosts some animal based shows like Sea Lion, Killer Whale and Dolphin show. The dolphin show is awesome and breathtaking. It also has animals kept for just watching. The animals are well trained and well behaved. So it is easy to interact with them. 
It also some of the best roller coaster rides like Electric Eel, Manta etc. You can enjoy with your family, as everyone has attraction according to their taste.
I have thoroughly enjoyed the park.Nice place to hang out with kids

Fun place for the kids and the weather could not have been nicer in January. We bought the all you can eat wristbands and the food was good. The lines were very long and sometimes you have to wait up to an hour in line to eat. Were the wristbands worth it? Maybe it was a break even? Probably a better deal when the park is open longer in the summer.

We had a great time!  We went on a Friday and the crowds weren't bad.  We hit up three shows (dolphins, sea lions/otters, and orcas) and they were all fun for kids and adults.  Lots of creatures to see and touch throughout the park as well as rides and play areas for all ages.

We brought in a few snacks to help our kids push through a bit longer.  We stopped at Mama Stella's for a late lunch and spent around $50 to feed four people.  About what you'd expect for amusement park fare.  There are bathrooms with changing tables and drinking fountains throughout the park.   We also had a stroller and for most of the  indoor exhibits/shows you will need to leave the stroller outside.

The roller coasters were surprisingly good!  We went on the Manta and Electric Eel.  Both really fun for those who meet the height requirement.  

I was not impressed by the parks cleanliness which is why I rated it four stars.

All in all, they do a great job entertaining and educating you about the animals in their care and I'd recommend a visit if you're looking for something to do in San Diego.

reviews.text: The best ever!  This is the one to do!  We saw thousands of dolphins and humpback up close. Totally bucket list check off. Beautiful huge sail boat. Helped raise the sails.  Felt like part of the crew looking for the whales. Amazing and friendly crew. Al was funny and personable.  Perfect for my 9 year old!  Good price and free snacks. Wonderful experience. If your trying to decide what boat to do I highly recommend this one!

By far the most outstanding customer service I have ever experienced! I booked this for my daughter and son in law who were visiting for her 30th birthday. It started with me emailing the company about planning a surprise for my daughter and ended up being the most beautiful gift ever. Fathom went way above and beyond to make this trip special. My kids said it was the most amazing thing they have ever experienced. They went into thinking they would not see anything and get sea sick and neither happened. No sea sickness and they saw whales, sea lions, and a pod of dolphins. She said it was her best birthday ever!

A lifelong memorable experience! We not only saw gray whales and rode with a huge pod of common dolphins, we also enjoyed Al's informative and fun talk .He was great and the ship is a stunning vessel to be aboard 👍My son and I enjoyed the Friday morning immensely ..AND we were treated to witnessing dolphin boat training.. F-18 taking off ..and the deployment of the USS Teddy Roosevelt aircraft carrier... AMAZING!! Cheers to the incredible crew and the incredible day!

AMAZING! Absolutely worth it, even if you don't see a whale. 

I was a little skeptical about this tour as things like this are typically very cheesy...not into that. However, it was NOT the case here at all here. 

This was classy and chill. 

My wife and I were in SD for the weekend and figured what the hell, let's give this a go. It did not disappoint! 

The crew was extremely friendly, knowledgeable, and helpful. They provided drinks and snacks at no cost too! 

It was a SMOOTH ride. Very low risk for seasickness. 

We did get to see a humpback whale so that was so cool! Honestly though, it was such an enjoyable and relaxing cruise, I wouldn't have cared much if we didn't see one. 

There are no actual seats on this ship because it is a true replica of The Yacht America from 1851. There are plenty of places to sit though!

We had THE most unbelievable time on Captain Troy’s sail / whale watching tour boat.  treated us like family and the perfect host and day with my family. Not to be missed experience if your looking for an adventure while in San Diego. I’d give 6 stars if I could.

reviews.text:
This park was a truly relaxing experience. We spent the last few hours of hour vacation here, before returning to the Midwest. The water was like bath water warm and the security made the environment feel rather safe.

It isn't far from Little Italy of looking for a nice bit to eat (vegan friendly options available as well) and the ships gave a wonderful view. Very calm, very relaxed and I would like to visit again soon.

Great place to visit. Lots of playgrounds. Water play area are great for kids especially on hot days. Lots of green space to picnic and enjoy the waterfront and scenery of the bay. Great artwork and classes. Awesome park. Very clean, secure, and good bathrooms.

Great place to hang out down by the harbor right off the ends of downtown. Kids can play in the water and they're is great space on the grass to hangout / picnic/ fly kites / sun bathe. Keep in mind though its right in front of the county building. Park is on the other side. Bathrooms are located at the top. Parking can be tight as it is downtown area.

Cool park across the Star of India ship downtown. Love the water display and the kids really enjoy the super tall slides and the spinning ride. My kids are aged 14, 6, 4 and 2 and they all enjoyed it.

This park is right outside SD County office on Harbour drive. This place has changed a lot in past two years. The addition of water play area is a hit amongst people of all groups. Kids to adults they just enjoy playing in the water or sitting with their toes dipped watching the ships sail by.
Also the play park and walking trails are well developed and positioned if someone wants to take a stroll. The underground parking lot is ideally located so that you do not have to cross any roads to reach this beautiful spot and is just a few steps away.
Must visit if you are visiting SD downtown.

reviews.text: My trip was Sept 21-25, 2019. IT WAS AMAZING! Shark Diver had every detail planned out down to the minute from start to finish. We saw sharks every day!! The best day was the 3rd day of diving because 2 other boats in the area had left so there was more shark activity. I booked the family room which was for two people. It had its own bathroom and was pretty spacious. Guadalupe Island is beautiful. We had beautiful weather the entire trip. The crew was super nice and made the trip so much more incredible. The only thing I wish I had done was to bring my own wetsuit tailored more towards my curves but the crew still made sure I was comfortable. I highly recommend this company and location for shark enthusiasts!

First paraplegic with this company. They went above and beyond to make sure I had an incredible experience. I would highly recommend Shark Diver to EVERYONE. If you are a thrill seeker or filling your bucket list, do yourself a favor and call Cindy at Shark Diver. Most amazing experience of my life and I have done a lot of outrageous things

Just completed an awesome trip to Guadalupe Island with Shark Diver.  Top notch trip all the way around.  Boat crew was awesome, food was good and bountiful and the sharks were spectacular.  Cabins were comfortable and the hot tub was a plus after a chilly dive.  I wouldn’t hesitate to recommend going with Shark Diver.  It was a memorable trip on all fronts - thanks to Shark Diver.

Awesome experience, whether watching from the deck above when they breach or from below in the cages, I was in awe of all the sharks seen. Martin gave great insight on how the Great White shark lives through out the excursion. I recommend this to anyone looking to go shark diving.

My husband and I just got back from our 1st time cage diving with great white sharks booked through Shark Diver with crew from Nautilus on the Undersea Hunter it was truly an amazing trip! Martin and Cindy with Shark Diver were willing to answer our questions both before and during our trip. There were plenty of options for cage time throughout the 3 days! They even provided go pro rentals so you could video your trip and at the end the crew with the help of photos from Martin made us an 8 minute slide show that we all were able to bring home. If you are at all interested in shark diving you should pick Shark diver who is a safe, reliable, well planned team that will coordinate your trip with the boat company and crew!

recommendations.address: 910 N Harbor Dr, San Diego, CA 92101, USA

google.name: USS Midway Museum
google.formatted_address: 910 N Harbor Dr, San Diego, CA 92101, USA

reviews.text: The USS midway what an amazing museum to go and see. I had so much fun with my wife on our trip to San Diego seeing all of the history that this aircraft Carrier holds. It was so crazy seeing how big a ship could be and how many people fit in there. One of the craziest things is how much food they go through every single day 13000 different Mills are served every single day . And it's crazy to think that our technology is improving even more allowing for bigger carriers and maybe even one day an aircraft Carrier that can go airborne and not just be in the ocean.

Wonderful "museum" of an aircraft carrier.  Included with admission is a listening device which works with a station at each attraction that was very informative. The best parts for me were the 2 live pilot presentations (each from the Vietnam war) on the catapult and the hook and arresting wire  (to stop the aircraft).  They each had excellent audio-visual aids as well. Don't miss this.

Besides the impressive huge scale of this ship, I was able to comprehend more in detail how The Midway used to be back in those years, it's amazing how planes were maintained, stored, etc, etc, I also noticed all the personnel working there makes it possible for me to enjoy to the max. One day is not enough to see all the great features this museum has. The planes are a great showroom to enjoy.
I am truly proud of this ship for the big effort carried on during WWII. I really suggest to read the history behind the great adventures and journeys went through.
You definitely will come back to see more.

The USS Midway was beyond any expectation. We were told to take our children and that we wouldn’t be disappointed.
My one boy is very tactile (nice word for touches everything .. TWICE) and the gentleman in the main engine room encouraged him to do just that!! He explained so much and just allowed him to enjoy the experience. My son was overjoyed!
A ton of history and a serial day packed full of so many things to see, touch and talk about. Would highly recommend taking the day to visit but be prepared to spend the ENTIRE day.

This is a great tour.  The ship is filled with interesting and educational displays highlighting the 47 years this ship was in service including two major renovations. Many of the aircraft that took off from the ship were on display.  It appears that many of the docents who serve on this ship were actually members of the crew at one time.  Almost all had a fascinating story to tell about some element or operation on the ship.  While not all of the ship was open to tour because of covid, we spent 4 hours and still didn't see everything available.  This museum makes for an incredible family experience.  I highly recommend it.  Every visitor will come away with some new knowledge and an appreciation for life in the military.

reviews.text:
Had a great experience wake boarding. I would suggest a private for 2 hours if you’re in a group between 2-5 people. We paid $360 for two hours and the boat was new and all the equipment was in great too.

They also offer different water sports making it a one stop shop for all your water sports!
We took a Paddleboarding course...amazing Guide Jacky! So much fun...

I can't recommend this place for surfing courses. I took the semester long intermediate surfing class and it was the worst surfing class I ever took. The surf instructors don't really teach, they kinda just hang out in the water. So if you really wanna learn surfing, I recommend not wasting your money on this but take a real surfing course somewhere else. The material and the facilities of this place are nice though

my son have a lower back pain do to the kind of work he does, he loves this place and he always take the whole family and somtimes friends to this spot and have an account with them, he rented a kayak yesterday and after 2 hours he returned it ,they made him take the kayak up to their storage area and put it on the rack for them,i wasn't so sure if thats their policy but he was in pain for just lifting that thing , he's not the kind a guy saying no if you ask him to do somthing but i'll contact some one to make sure that's part of the rental agreement.....

Would strongly recommend this place for anyone who is looking to get out for a quick wakeboard set while in the San Diego area. They have brand new nautique boats. I was fortunate enough to ride behind a 2019 Nautique GS. The instructor, Hunter, did a great job helping the newer ride on the boat. Not only that he made sure we had the right gear, so that everyone had a marvelous time!
